Unlike most UC Davis students, Evan Beecher spent much of high school in Davis, and knew the area well in advance. Transferring to UC Davis from the Bay Area in late 2003, Beecher is a Political Science major with also a large interest in history. Beecher, along with Vice Presidential candidate and friend Ryan Basilio, ran as an Independent for the ASUCD Presidency in the Winter 2004 elections. The http://www.californiaaggie.com/media/storage/paper981/news/2004/02/19/FrontPage/Candidate.Profile.Evan.Beecher.And.Ryan.Basilio1316573.shtml BeecherBasilio ticket earned 450 votes, ending up in a close http://davischoicevoting.org/asucddata/winter04/winter2004overview.txt third place.

Beechers politics are best described as fiscally libertarian but socially centerleft.

He likes his coffee blackespecially the coffee Users/MilesHookey makes for him at his placeand finds French history boring.

Beecher is also a descendent of the esteemed American novelist wiki:WikiPedia:Harriet_Beecher_Stowe Harriet Beecher Stowe, the writer of Uncle Toms Cabin.

